title: Pajama Pajimjams
description: Oscar pretends to be a talking pair of pajamas named "Jimjams" to make his friend Pajamas happy.

title: A Patch of Perturbed Petunias
description: Share fears she's losing her ability as a problem-solver and peacemaker when she can't calm a squabble between a group of Whiffles and a flower bed of Perturbed Petunias. Cheer discovers it's not Share's fault; the Petunias are being secretly manipulated by Bluster's rumor-mongering.

title: Haunted Campfire
description: The campers must battle ghosts of their own creation after their scary stories mysteriously come true.

title: The Library
description: The campers spend a rainy day at the library.

title: Moon Problems
description: The Moon gets sad when Oscar loses his friendship bracelet.

title: The Curse of Elmore
description: When Gumball's schoolfriend Leslie finds an old video tape, the creepy mystery of Elmore's ghostly past unfolds. Featuring spooky and hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Puff Paint
description: Oscar's painting is unpopular so he goes on a journey of self-discovery.

title: Pajamas Party
description: When Pajamas starts to panic that Oscar will outgrow her, Oscar tries to help but things go awry.

title: Director's Cut
description: Oscar receives a camcorder from his parents and sets out to prove to them the magic on the island is real.

title: The Beepers: The Visitor
description: The Beepers find the perfect groove after a new friend shreds a little too hard.

title: Catfight
description: The princesses Looma and Attea are at odds over who gets to marry Ben!

title: Time Traveling Quick Pants
description: Oscar and Hedgehog learn about a quicksand that lets them go back in time.

title: Cosmic Bupkiss
description: A storm blocks Oscar and Hedgehog's one chance to see a comet.

title: Wide Load Vacay: Dumbrella
description: Two houses, Frank and Charlie, have been traveling on the back of a truck in the rain for days. Charlie produces an umbrella to help his friend but unfortunately it's a "dumbrella" and it's looking to have some fun with them!

title: The Vampire Strikes Back
description: Ben, Rook, and Rad Dudesman come face to face with the evil Lord Transyl, a vampire-like alien who can make anyone his loyal slave! (Introducing new Ben alien, Whampire.)

title: Elmore's Most Wanted
description: Gumball's dad has been revealed as "Elmore's Most Wanted" - but when the Chief of Police tries to investigate, things do not go according to plan. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Clayton
description: Darwin needs to find a photo of Clayton to put on the cover of the school yearbook - but he makes the mistake of seeking help from Tobias, who has his eye on the cover spot himself! Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Monster Visit
description: The monsters get nervous when their Godmonster comes for a visit.

title: Twelve Angry Hedgehogs
description: Hedgehog wants to win the Golden Science Badge but runs into some unexpected competition.

title: Space Invasion
description: A visit from Puddle the alien tests the limit of Oscar's hosting skills.

title: Pepper's Blanket Is Missing
description: Pepper's blanket goes missing at a cabin sleepover.

title: Sarah
description: Darwin asks Sarah for a photo to put on the cover of the school yearbook. But when Sarah tries to help, things get a little sticky. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Fuzzy Pink Time Babies
description: Oscar and Hedgehog learn how to stop time.

title: Wide Load Vacay: Big City Dancers
description: Two houses, Frank and Charlie, traveling on the back of a truck visit NYC where the rhythms of the city make Charlie wanna dance his little back porch off. Frank … not so much. But when you go far enough into the city, anything can happen.

title: Mop Forever
description: At Alice's dress-up party the campers are magically turned into their costumes.

title: Collect This
description: Ben finally meets the ones responsible for his intergalactic TV show, and the actor who makes Ben 10 more famous than Ben himself!

title: Computer Vampire
description: Oscar finds a mysterious old video game in the library.

title: Feeling Spacey
description: Oscar and Hedgehog arrive on a planet that has no emotions.

title: We Baby Bears: BHA Bha Song
description: We Baby Bears follows baby bear brothers Grizz, Panda, and Ice Bear as they journey in a magical box to fantastic different worlds in search of their perfect home.

title: Rain, Rain Go Away
description: After Grumpy's anger sends his belly badge out of control with a thunderstorm that floods a newly-planted Whiffle meadow, he vows to never be grumpy again. Renaming himself "Mr. Happy," he drives everyone crazy with niceness. When the Whiffles desperately need his clouds to make rain and Mr. Happy can't deliver, Cheer and the team must get him back in touch with his inner grump.

title: Alan
description: Darwin wants to put Alan on the cover of the school yearbook - but Alan's apparent modesty gets in the way. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The First Day
description: Best friends Oscar and Hedgehog get dropped off at their first day at summer camp.

title: The Beepers: Funky Time
description: The Beepers play with tempo and learn that adapting to change can be…sweaty.

title: Popular Banana Split
description: Hedgehog and Max discover a tiny high school when they are accidentally shrunk by a science experiment.

title: Alpha Bodies
description: Cartoonito presents Alpha Bodies! It's time to use our bodies to make every letter of the alphabet, from A to Z, but one over-eager letter keeps getting ahead of itself.

title: Chocolate Money Badgers
description: Oscar learns that he can earn merit badges that unlock prizes.

title: Banana Joe
description: When Principal Brown sets Darwin the task of making the school yearbook, Darwin starts by asking class clown Banana Joe for a simple selfie to put on the cover. But with Banana Joe, things are never that simple. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Vote Gumball…and Penny?
description: Gumball is running for School President and is looking for a worthy running mate. When he asks his girlfriend Penny, he does not get the answer he expects. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Mother's Day
description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais need to find the perfect Mother's Day gift. Will it be a cute card, a thoughtful painting or something entirely different? Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: The Soundhouse
description: Oscar and Hedgehog discover a new structure on the island and become friends with its caretaker.

title: Perfect Day
description: Ben thinks he's having 'the perfect day' only to realize he's been put in a dream world by Enoch and the Forever Knights who are after the Omnitrix. Ben's "dream world" soon becomes a nightmare world, with Ben forced to live out his ultimate terror...being stuck at school! But with Max and Gwen's help, he's able to vanquish his nightmare foes and re-enter the real world where he takes down  Enoch...only to reveal an even more powerful knight...The Forever King.

title: I Heart Heartforde
description: Oscar, hedgehog and the other campers are excited to take a trip to the non-magical town of Heartforde.

title: Campers Above the Bed
description: Hedgehog finds a city underneath her bed as she looks for her missing diary.

title: Return to Forever
description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

title: A Yoorg Awakening
description: Funshine's jokes unwittingly hurt the feelings of a strange Rock Giant. Disturbed from its slumber, the usually benign creature inadvertently creates havoc for the Whiffles until Funshine calms it by apologizing.

title: Ice Cream Headache
description: The campers get magical powers from the witches supply of magic ice cream.

title: Hello Around the World
description: Cartoonito presents Hello Around the World! All across the globe, friends greet each other in lots of different languages. Watch along and discover some of the many ways to say "Hello," around the world and beyond!

title: The Beepers: Spotlight
description: When a spotlight gives everyone a chance to solo, a shy Beeper discovers the courage to shine.

title: CN Special: NBA All-Star Slam Dunk Contest
description: Cartoon Network's version of the NBA Slam Dunk Contest, highlighting the best slam dunks, hosted by the Teen Titans.

title: Susie's Fantastical Scavenger Hunt
description: Oscar and Hedgehog must learn to exist without each other when they are put on different teams during a scavenger hunt.

title: Saxophone Come Home
description: Oscar befriends a teenage Yeti.

title: Charmed, I'm Sure
description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

title: Rad Monster Party
description: Ben and Rook enlist the help of intergalactic smuggler Rad Dudesman to fly them through the Anur System, the home of the monstrous aliens!

title: Wide Load Vacay: Eye Spy
description: Two houses, Frank and Charlie, are traveling on the back of a truck from Montana to Utah. Charlie wants to play a game of Eye Spy. He finds more and more obvious objects for Frank to spy but Frank isn't quite getting the hang of it. Yet!

title: Mr. Softball
description: Susie challenges the campers to a game of softball to get out of doing a chore.

title: Don't Drink the Water
description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

title: The Basketball Liaries
description: With the help from Basketball, Oscar makes an impressive shot that scores him a spot on the Gold League.

title: Momsoon
description: Hedgehog gets a call during her radio show from someone who needs her help.

title: Food Around the Corner
description: Ben as Gravattack attempts to moderate a fragile peace treaty, but must endure the attacks of tiny alien fleas, which have inhabited his body.

title: Susie Appreciation Day
description: Hedgehog and Oscar find themselves trapped in Susie's cabin and must escape undetected.

title: It's My Party
description: Oscar and Hedgehog plan a surprise birthday party for Susie.

title: Carrie
description: Darwin sets out to find a photo of Carrie for the cover of the school yearbook - but they end up reminiscing about all their past spooky shenanigans. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Hedgehog Werewolf
description: Hedgehog gets bit by a cute puppy and is starting to act strange.

title: Ghost the Boy
description: Oscar and Hedgehog befriend a ghost who can't remember who he is.

title: Sneeze Guard
description: Oscar and Hedgehog must work with the witches to cure Alice's camp-threatening illness.

title: Radio Silence
description: Oscar must get Hedgehog a special sandwich in order to save their friendship.

title: The Great Elf Invention Convention
description: Oscar, Max, and Hedgehog do a favor for Barb the elf in exchange for some chips.

title: Oscar & Hedgehog's Melody
description: Susie holds the annual talent show that has the rest of the campers competing to win.

title: Divided We Stand
description: While at the beach, Ben discovers a new hero, Ditto, and soon has the ability to create multiple Dittos at once. These multiple Dittos can't agree on anything and drive Gwen crazy. However when the chips are down, these Dittos come together as one fighting force in order to defeat Animo and his army of replicant Stinkflies.

title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 2
description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

title: Waffle Cones for Whiffles
description: The Whiffles are too hot and tired to work because their daily treat, colorful ice in Waffles Cones delivered by the whimsical "Icelings," hasn't arrived - the Icelings have mysteriously disappeared. As the Care Bears search for them, Share volunteers to make the treats. It's much more than she can handle but she's determined to go-it-alone and not ask for help. Things get out of hand and Share ends up snared in Bluster's trap with the Icelings, who help her to realize that we get more done when we work together.

title: Monster Babies
description: Alice lures Oscar and his monster friends for a tea party, but only to turn the monsters into cute babies.

title: Nobody's Perfect
description: When Cheer makes some simple mistakes, she begins to lose confidence in her piloting skills and herself. The self-doubt becomes so severe, she decides to step away from her role as pilot of the Cloudseeker. But the Team needs her, the Whiffles need her, and she must regain her self-confidence so they can stop Bluster's latest nefarious scheme.

title: Ancestor Act
description: When Gumball's sister Anais researches the Watterson family tree, she uncovers a long history of nonsense. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

title: Midnight Quittance
description: Ramona invites Hedgehog and Oscar to participate in a special holiday ritual.

title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 3
description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

title: Spell Crushers
description: Hedgehog tries to get over a crush so she can regain her focus on magic.
